The paper discusses privacy-preserving techniques for distributed computation in network monitoring, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of data structures like Bloom Filters and bitmap strings, which are commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the scalability and efficiency of the proposed approach, which are important topics in database systems (cs.DB) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
